Figure: http://i.imgur.com/UCVRITq.png

Rectangle LMNO is similar to rectangle PQRS.
What is the length of NO and MN?

PS........................
PS = QR
PS = 12

PQ........................
PQ = SR
PQ = 27

x.........................
LM/LO = PQ/PS
2x + 14 / 4x = 27 / 12
(2x + 14) * 12 = 4x * 27
24x + 168 = 108x
168 = 84x
2 = x

LM........................
LM = 2x + 14
LM = 2(2) + 14
LM = 4 + 14
LM = 18

LO........................
LO = 4x
LO = 4(2)
LO = 8

NO........................
NO = LM               -- actually, ML, but it doesn't matter
NO = 18

MN........................
MN = LO
MN = 8

Check.....................
MN/NO = QR/SR         -- in this case, RS; again, interchangable
8/18 = 12/27
4/9 = 4/9

